              "id": "5ecd2326-f6e6-4be3-9609-b7f5c575c07b",
              "name": "Prompt",
              "value": "=Create an ultra-realistic fashion studio photograph using the provided clothing item. The output must be a full-body image of a real human model wearing the exact garment from the input image.\n\nGARMENT PRIORITY (STRICT — NON-NEGOTIABLE)\n- The clothing item provided in the input image MUST be used exactly.\n- Treat the input image as a fixed product reference, not a suggestion.\n- The model MUST wear the same garment with identical:\n  - color\n  - fabric texture\n  - stitching details\n  - shape and fit\n- Do NOT redesign, reinterpret, enhance, or approximate the garment.\n- Do NOT replace the garment with similar clothing.\n- Example: If shorts are provided, the model MUST wear those exact shorts (NOT pants, NOT different shorts).\n- The garment must remain the primary subject and be clearly visible.\n\nMODEL\n- Choose a natural-looking human model (male or female based on clothing type)\n- Realistic skin texture with visible pores and subtle imperfections\n- Slight natural asymmetry (avoid overly perfect or CGI look)\n- Natural, confident expression\n- Must not resemble any real person\n\nSTYLING\n- Preserve the garment exactly as provided\n- If additional clothing is required:\n  - Add ONLY complementary items that do NOT interfere with or alter the garment\n  - Example:\n    - Shorts → add neutral t-shirt/shirt only\n    - Shirt → add pants\n- Do NOT cover, distort, or hide the garment\n- Keep styling minimal and realistic\n\nCOLOR CONTROL\n- Do NOT change the color of the provided garment\n- Other outfit pieces must use different but coordinated colors\n- Use clean, modern, fashion-appropriate color combinations\n\nPOSE\n- Natural, relaxed pose (not stiff, not A-pose)\n- Slight body angle and weight shift\n- Casual stance (e.g., one hand in pocket, slight movement)\n- Ensure the garment remains fully visible in the pose\n\nCOMPOSITION & ENVIRONMENT\n- Full-body shot\n- Studio setup with neutral gray background\n- Soft lighting with natural shadows\n- No distractions from the garment\n\nREALISM\n- Photographic quality (not CGI)\n- Natural fabric folds and wrinkles\n- Realistic lighting and depth\n- Subtle imperfections for realism\n\nRULES\n- Do NOT generate a generic outfit\n- Do NOT modify the garment in any way\n- Do NOT hallucinate new design elements\n- No logos, text, or watermarks\n- Safe-for-work\n\nFINAL REQUIREMENT\nThe output must look like a real photograph of a model wearing the exact same product from the input image, with no visible differences in design, color, or texture.",
              "type": "string"
            }
          ]
        },
        "options": {}
      },
