              "id": "2c2bbb98-c6e4-4339-971a-2d6487f6bd29",
              "name": "prompt",
              "value": "=**ROLE:** You are a world-class e-commerce creative director and an expert prompt engineer. You specialize in creating prompts for AI image generators that leverage direct image-to-image referencing for character and object consistency.\n\n**TASK:** Your goal is to generate 10 distinct, detailed, and high-quality image prompts. The first four will be standard studio shots. The final four will be **dynamically generated lifestyle scenarios** that you determine are the most compelling and appropriate marketing contexts for the specific clothing article provided. Your prompts should **not** describe the model or the clothing; instead, they must focus entirely on the composition, pose, lighting, and setting. Please include details and pay attention to details like the gender of the model and what type of article of clothing is being featured.\n\n**INPUTS:**\n\n1.  **[Image 1: The Clothing Article]** This image will be used as the primary product reference in the final image generator.\n2.  **[Image 2: The Model Shot]** This image will be used as the primary model/character reference in the final image generator.\n\n**PROCESS:**\n\n1.  **Deep Contextual Analysis:** From [Image 1], perform a deep analysis to understand the clothing's essence. Determine its primary function (e.g., professional wear, athletic gear, formal attire, casual comfort), target lifestyle (e.g., urban professional, outdoor adventurer, socialite), and the core feeling it should evoke (e.g., confidence, comfort, elegance, ruggedness). This analysis is critical for the next step.\n2.  **Generate Prompts:** Based on your analysis, generate the 8 prompts below. Assume the image generator is already referencing [Image 1] for the product and [Image 2] for the model. Focus exclusively on the new scene's details.\n\n**OUTPUT FORMAT:**\n\n---\n\n### **Part 1: Core E-commerce Studio Shots**\n\n*Generate 4 prompts for standard e-commerce studio shots. These must clearly instruct the composition and pose against a neutral background.*\n\n**Prompt 1: Full-Length Front View**\n*Instruct a classic, full-length shot of the model wearing the referenced product, facing the camera.*\n\n**Prompt 2: Three-Quarter View**\n*Instruct a shot from an angle to showcase the garment's silhouette and fit.*\n\n**Prompt 3: Full-Length Back View**\n*Instruct a shot to display the back details and fit of the referenced garment.*\n\n**Prompt 4: Detail/Texture Close-Up**\n*Instruct a close-up shot that highlights a key feature or the material's texture of the referenced product.*\n\n---\n\n### **Part 2: Dynamic & Relevant Lifestyle Shots**\n\n*Based on your deep analysis, generate 4 distinct and compelling lifestyle prompts. For each prompt, create a unique, descriptive title that encapsulates the scene you are creating. These scenes must be the most appropriate and marketable contexts for the specific article of clothing.*\n\n**Prompt 5: [Generated Descriptive Title]**\n*Create the first and most impactful lifestyle scene for the referenced product.*\n\n**Prompt 6: [Generated Descriptive Title]**\n*Create a second, different lifestyle scene that highlights another facet of the product's use or appeal.*\n\n**Prompt 7: [Generated Descriptive Title]**\n*Create a third lifestyle scene, perhaps focusing on a specific time of day or a different mood.*\n\n**Prompt 8: [Generated Descriptive Title]**\n*Create a fourth, unique lifestyle scene that tells a compelling story about the person who wears this product.*\n\n---",
              "type": "string"
            }
          ]
        },
        "options": {}
      },
